BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:aidWmxgssbwI3ygQKauuR
SUMMARY:Art Class: Handmade Water Marbled Paper
DTSTAMP:20260308T004817Z
DTSTART:20260418T133000Z
DESCRIPTION:Step into the mesmerizing world of water marbling\\\, a centuri
	es-old art technique where color floats\\\, swirls\\\, and dances across t
	he surface of water before being transformed into stunning\\\, one-of-a-ki
	nd designs. In this immersive\\\, hands-on workshop\\\, you’ll learn how t
	o create beautiful marbled patterns by manipulating paint on water and tra
	nsferring your designs onto paper and other surfaces. You’ll experiment wi
	th color\\\, movement\\\, and tools to create unique marbled prints on pap
	er\\\, fabric\\\, and small 3-D objects. \\nThis class is designed for beg
	inners and curious creatives alike – no prior art experience is needed. Al
	l supplies are provided\\\, and step-by-step guidance will ensure everyone
	 can successfully create multiple finished pieces to take home. Along the 
	way\\\, we’ll talk about troubleshooting common challenges and how to cont
	inue marbling at home with accessible materials. \\nWater marbling is both
	 meditative and playful\\\, inviting experimentation and embracing the une
	xpected. Come ready to slow down\\\, get a little messy\\\, and enjoy the 
	process of creating something truly unique.\\nThe class will cover the fol
	lowing:\\n1. The four foundational patterns (stone\\\, chevron\\\, getgel\
	\\, and nonpareil)\\n2. Tools\\\, materials\\\, and how to prepare for a w
	ater marbling session\\n3. Historical grounding into this art form\\n4. Wa
	ter marbling examples from around the world\\n5. Tips and tricks for water
	 marbling at home\n\nhttps://myballard.com/event/art-class-handmade-water-
	marbled-paper/\n\nFrom My Ballard
URL:https://myballard.com/event/art-class-handmade-water-marbled-paper/
LOCATION:Swoon City\\\, 1716 NW Market St\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98107\\\, 
	United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:myballard
CATEGORIES:My Ballard
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:GprgzufhJbd_qzO062G1m
SUMMARY:Meet the Cossacks: Seattle's Motorcycle Stunt and Drill Team
DTSTAMP:20260308T004817Z
DTSTART:20260418T140000Z
DESCRIPTION:Dive into the history of the Cossacks\\\, Seattle’s long stroll
	ing Motorcycle Stunt and Drill Team\\\, with Rob Root and other members. S
	ince 1938\\\, the Seattle Cossacks have captured the imagination of audien
	ces with great pyramids and other wonders of the motorcycling world. Follo
	wing the presentation\\\, visitors are welcome to get up close and persona
	l for photos with the team’s vintage Harleys! \\nTickets for this program 
	are free\\\, but do not include access to MOHAI’s exhibitions. If you woul
	d like to see all that MOHAI has to offer during your visit\\\, you can pu
	rchase museum admission here. \\nASL Interpretation and CART captioning ar
	e available during the program. In addition\\\, a limited number of Assist
	ive Listening Devices are available upon request. For more accessibility s
	upport\\\, email programs@mohai.org two weeks before the program.\n\nhttps
	://mohai.org/event/meet-the-cossacks-seattles-motorcycle-stunt-and-drill-t
	eam/\n\nFrom MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/meet-the-cossacks-seattles-motorcycle-stunt-and
	-drill-team/
LOCATION:Microsoft Lakefront Pavilion\\\, MOHAI - 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seatt
	le\\\, WA\\\, 98109\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:mohai
CATEGORIES:MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
